# React Rules

## Components

- Use functional components exclusively
- Use named exports for components
- Keep components focused and single-purpose
- Extract logic to custom hooks when reusable

## Hooks

- Follow Rules of Hooks strictly
- Use `useMemo` and `useCallback` only when necessary (proven performance issue)
- Prefer `useReducer` over `useState` for complex state

## Patterns

```tsx
// Preferred component structure
import { type FC } from 'react';

interface UserCardProps {
  name: string;
  email: string;
}

export const UserCard: FC<UserCardProps> = ({ name, email }) => {
  return (
    <div>
      <h2>{name}</h2>
      <p>{email}</p>
    </div>
  );
};
```

## Avoid

- Class components
- Default exports for components
- Inline styles (use Blueprint classes or CSS modules)
- Direct DOM manipulation

